1{-# OPTIONS_GHC -Wall #-}
2
3-- | Complex content type.
4
5module Koshucode.Baala.Data.Content.Complex
6  ( -- * Complex contents
7    -- ** Collection
8    CList (..),
9    CSet (..), gSetSort,
10    -- ** Relational
11    CTie (..),
12    CRel (..), dee, dum,
13    CInterp (..),
14    -- ** Type
15    CType (..),
16  ) where
17
18import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Base                    as B
19import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Syntax                  as S
20import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Data.Type               as D
21import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Data.Content.Singleton  as D
22
23
24-- --------------------------------------------  Complex contents
25
26-- ----------------------  List
27
28-- | List of contents.
29class (D.CTypeOf c) => CList c where
30    isList      ::       c -> Bool
31    gList       ::       c -> [c]
32    pList       ::     [c] -> c
33
34    getList     ::  B.Ab c -> B.Ab [c]
35    getList     =   D.getAbAb isList gList
36
37    putList     ::     [c] -> B.Ab c
38    putList     =    Right . pList
39
40-- ----------------------  Set
41
42-- | Set of contents.
43class (D.CTypeOf c) => CSet c where
44    isSet       ::          c -> Bool
45    gSet        ::          c -> [c]
46    pSet        ::        [c] -> c
47
48    getSet      ::     B.Ab c -> B.Ab [c]
49    getSet      =      D.getAbAb isSet gSet
50
51    putSet      ::        [c] -> B.Ab c
52    putSet      =       Right . pSet
53
54gSetSort :: (Ord c, CSet c) => c -> [c]
55gSetSort = B.sort . gSet
56
57-- ----------------------  Tie
58
59-- | Tie of terms.
60class (D.CTypeOf c) => CTie c where
61    isTie       ::           c -> Bool
62    gTie        ::           c -> [S.Term c]
63    pTie        ::  [S.Term c] -> c
64
65    getTie      ::      B.Ab c -> B.Ab [S.Term c]
66    getTie      =       D.getAbAb isTie gTie
67
68    putTie      ::  [S.Term c] -> B.Ab c
69    putTie      =  Right . pTie
70
71-- ----------------------  Rel
72
73-- | Relation of terms.
74class (D.CTypeOf c) => CRel c where
75    isRel       ::           c -> Bool
76    gRel        ::           c -> D.Rel c
77    pRel        ::     D.Rel c -> c
78
79    getRel      ::      B.Ab c -> B.Ab (D.Rel c)
80    getRel      =       D.getAbAb isRel gRel
81
82    putRel      ::     D.Rel c -> B.Ab c
83    putRel      =      Right . pRel
84
85-- | Nullary full relation.
86dee :: (CRel c) => c
87dee = pRel D.reldee
88
89-- | Nullary empty relation.
90dum :: (CRel c) => c
91dum = pRel D.reldum
92
93-- ----------------------  Interp
94
95-- | Data intepretation.
96class (D.CTypeOf c) => CInterp c where
97    isInterp    ::           c -> Bool
98    gInterp     ::           c -> D.Interp
99    pInterp     ::    D.Interp -> c
100
101    getInterp   ::      B.Ab c -> B.Ab D.Interp
102    getInterp   =       D.getAbAb isInterp gInterp
103
104    putInterp   ::    D.Interp -> B.Ab c
105    putInterp   =     Right . pInterp
106
107-- ----------------------  Type
108
109-- | Type of content.
110class (D.CTypeOf c) => CType c where
111    isType      ::           c -> Bool
112    gType       ::           c -> D.Type
113    pType       ::      D.Type -> c
114
115    getType     ::      B.Ab c -> B.Ab D.Type
116    getType     =       D.getAbAb isType gType
117
118    putType     ::      D.Type -> B.Ab c
119    putType     =       Right . pType
120
